sense.name: finish an activity or process, either physical or abstract
sense.examples: I finally completed stripping the wood in the living room. John completed the 100 meter race in his fastest time ever. I haven't finished completing my application for college. Would you complete this questionaire for me?

sense.name: carry out an assigned task or duty
sense.examples: The soldiers must complete their current tour of duty. That team has completed the most passes this season.

sense.name: make whole, add a missing part to a given whole
sense.examples: Matching shoes and handbag completed the ensemble. A gold medal at the Olympics would complete his achievements in gymnastics.
